23 502.130) Under existing law, whenever tags are required for any species of wildlife, it is
24 unlawful to possess any of that species without the correct tag. (NRS 502.150) Section 3 of
25 this bill authorizes a person, for non-commercial purposes and without the required tag, to
26 [take or] gather shed antlers or a skull or head , with or without antlers or horns attached,
27 or bones from the carcass of any wildlife species for which a tag is required [, with or
28 without antlers or horns attached.] under certain circumstances.
29 Existing law requires the Board of Wildlife Commissioners to adopt regulations for
30 the taking of antlers which have been naturally shed by any big game mammal in this
31 State. (NRS 503.655) Section 4 of this bill instead requires the Commission to adopt
32 regulations for the gathering of shed antlers which must only apply to the gathering of
33 shed antlers for commercial purposes.
